IDEA: Numbers are very important and powerful in the Scripted Fates continuity. As such, certain forces have learned how to harness and use these powers for highly unorthodox manners.

The typical arrangement of a number sequences is 1-2-3-4. To introduce a high level of "separation" to create a Seperatist Sequence, you must separate each number from what it's meant to be paired with.
1 is best paired next to 0 and 2. 2 is paired next to 1 and 3. It's a chain, and breaking that chain yields certain "effects" that those "certain forces" use, mainly Nul Detta, vicars of null, and even the Arch of Sentients.
The typical Seperatist Sequence goes as follows: 2-4-1-3
By repeating this pattern of separating the numbers from their "best pair" just enough to where no single number will ever be positioned next to a pair, you can have this sequence repeat endlessly.
2-4-1-3-6-8-5-7-0-2-9-1-4-6-3-5-8-0-7-9-(2-4-1-3) <- this is where the sequence often starts looping.

